column15: Swiss Agency for Development and Cooperation (SDC)
column17: Programme d’Hydraulique Rurale – Appui Au Secteur Eau et Assainissement (PHRASEA) Phase 2
column20: Moins de 50% des nigériens ont accès à l’eau potable et seuls 7% disposent de conditions d'assainissement de base. La croissance démographique galopante\, la dispersion de la population sur le territoire et la précarité des finances publiques sont des contraintes empêchant l'accès des populations à ces services de base. Le PHRASEA vient en appui aux efforts du gouvernement\, en misant sur la maitrise d’ouvrage des communes.

column17: PSD Toolkit
column20: The various Apps in the toolbox can assist embassies in their efforts to create a business-enabling environment\, remove trade barriers and in matching local and Dutch business partners\, in order to shape the local implementation of the Dutch agenda for Aid\, Trade and Investment. Matchmaking\, Government to Government assistance\, training of managers and entrepreneurs\, trade missions to and from developing countries\, transfer of knowledge between educational or knowledge institutions such as universities in a given country and in the Netherlands are some examples of these initiatives.
column27: Netherlands Enterprise Agency,Netherlands Ministry of Foreign Affairs,Netherlands Enterprise Agency

Matchmaking\, Government to Government assistance\, training of managers and entrepreneurs\, trade missions to and from developing countries\, transfer of knowledge between educational or knowledge institutions such as universities in a given country and in the Netherlands are some examples of these initiatives.

column17: Dutch Risk Reduction Team (DRR Team) Phase 2
column20: The Dutch Risk Reduction Team (DRR Team)\, with a swift response team of experts\, advises governments on how to resolve urgent water issues related to flood risks\, water pollution and water supply\, to prevent disasters or to rebuild after water related disasters. The Netherlands Enterprise Agency administers DRR Team at the request of the Netherlands Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the Netherlands Ministry of Infrastructure and Water management.
column27: Netherlands Enterprise Agency,Netherlands Ministry of Foreign Affairs,Netherlands Enterprise Agency

column17: Dutch Surge Support (DSS Water)   Phase 2
column20: The Dutch Surge Support (DSS water) responds to the needs during water related disasters around the globe by deploying excellent experts from the Dutch water sector. With this facility the Netherlands aims to contribute to a better international response to water and sanitation related disasters and assist in building up knowledge in dealing with these emergencies. Netherlands Enterprise Agency administers DRR at the request of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of The Netherlands and the Ministry of Infrastructure and Environment.

column17: Satellite Based Water Monitoring and Flow Forecasting (Implementation Phase)
column20: The project consists of the following elements:- Implementation of the satellite based Energy and Water Balance Monitoring System (EWBMS) which on a daily basis will provide climatic data fields of temperature  radiation evapotranspiration and precipitation- Implementation of the Large Scale Hydrological Model (LSHM) which uses the data from the EWBMS to generate river flow rates and forecasts- Implementation of the Drought Monitoring System (DMS) which will provide meteorological hydrological agricultural and climatological drought information for the entire basin- Testing calibration validation and optimisation of the systems provided- Creation and training of an operational satellite monitoring unit at NBA responsible for operating these systems and diffusing the data and related information products among users in the member countries-Training of users.
column27: Invest International,Invest International,EARS B.V.,eLEAF B.V.,Niger Basin Authority,Ministère de l'Eau et de l'Environnement

column15: Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Netherlands
column17: NIA Promotion l'agriculture productive
column20: Le programme «Promotion de l'agriculture productive» fait partie du programme de coopération économique de «Développement rural et a griculture productive» au sein du secteur «Agriculture productive et sécurité alimentaire» de la coopérative allemande avec le Niger. Ce programme a démarré en 2011. La demande concerne une coopération déléguée avec la GIZ\, avec une demande d'un montant de 4 millions (2 MEURO mars 2020\, encore 2 MEURO pour 2021). L'objectif du programme est de faire en sorte que le secteur agricole au Niger contribue davantage à la croissance économique nationale et à la sécurité alimentaire par l'irrigation à petite échelle. L'accès à une irrigation stable encourage la diversification des produits agricoles et prolonge la période de production. Cela entraîne à son tour une plus grande autonomie et une augmentation des revenus.
